eing removed for deprecated APIs. Adding actor-typed could also mask the scope, which is a concern. It's important to keep things concise and to mention the deterministic setup without dependencies, including pekko-actor-typed. I want to ensure that my summary is short and that it’s a valid single JSON without any markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"pekko-actor_2.13 is a standalone actor library; its POM only adds scala-library and typesafe-config, normal usage does not require external services, Docker, or extra test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No extra environment variables or system properties are required for ordinary ActorSystem/Props/config usage. When updating the existing tests for 2.0.0-M1, do not use the removed classic TypedActor APIs such as org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedProps, or TypedActorExtension; pekko-actor-typed_2.13 is a different typed-actor API and should not be added merely to restore those removed classes. If DNS internals are still covered, keep the existing --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED JVM/native-image build argument pattern.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"2.0.0-M1 removed many deprecated APIs, including the classic TypedActor classes present in 1.1.5, so stale tests will fail at Scala compilation rather than needing setup.\",\n    \"Adding pekko-actor-typed_2.13 would broaden the tested surface beyond org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13 and would not restore org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04ec4981cc4e0a8b016a42bf758da88190a92ea75682e07897\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6941, "output": 622, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27019, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 178275927